ul.li:
Search-performance. The took parameter indicates the number of milliseconds required for the search;
while fields within the _shards object indicate how many Elasticsearch shards were available for search,
how many were accessed successfully, and how many unsuccessfully.

section.p:
The contents of the _id field, returned from an Elasticsearch 
query, can be used to retrieve the entire corresponding document 
from Couchbase. Ensure Couchbase is running; then, proceed as follows:

